<b>Jonathan Wells (2006) <i>The Politically Incorrect Guide to Darwinism and Intelligent Design</i>. Regnery Publishing, Inc. Washington, DC.</b><sup><a href="amazon://1596980133">Amazon</a></sup>

<b>Synopsis:</b> One thing is for sure, Jonathan Wells is too modest.  His recently published, <i>The Politically Incorrect Guide to Darwinism and Intelligent Design</i>, is not only politically incorrect but incorrect in most other ways as well: scientifically, logically, historically, legally, academically, and morally.

